{"lemma":"سامٍّ","slug":"سامٍّ","root":"س.م.م","root_slug":"س-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20614","n20830","n21329"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8D%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"high, lofty"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"exalted, sublime"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"emanating from the sultan or vizier"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"poisonous, toxic"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rove, to pasture (camels, sheep, birds …)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to offer for sale"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to urge, to demand, to compel, to impose, to afflict, etc.","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذْ أَنْجَيْنَاكُمْ مِنْ آلِ فِرْعَوْنَ يَسُومُونَكُمْ سُوءَ الْعَذَابِ ۖ يُقَتِّلُونَ أَبْنَاءَكُمْ وَيَسْتَحْيُونَ نِسَاءَكُمْ ۚ وَفِي ذَٰلِكُم بَلَاءٌ مِنْ رَبِّكُمْ عَظِيمٌ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ordain for ecclesiastical office"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Shem"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Sam"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"death","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ رُمْحِ بْنِ ٱلْمُهَاجِرِ، أَخْبَرَنَا ٱللَّيْثُ، عَنْ عُقَيْلٍ، عَنِ ٱبْنِ شِهَابٍ، أَخْبَرَنِي أَبُو سَلَمَةَ بْنُ عَبْدِ ٱلرَّحْمَنِ وَسَعِيدُ بْنُ ٱلْمُسَيَّبِ، أَنَّ أَبَا هُرَيْرَةَ أَخْبَرَهُمَا أَنَّهُ سَمِعَ رَسُولَ ٱللَّٰهِ—صَلَّى ٱللَّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ—يَقُولُ: «إِنَّ فِي ٱلْحَبَّةِ ٱلسَّوْدَاءِ شِفَاءً مِنْ كُلِّ دَاءٍ إِلَّا ٱلسَّامَ». وَٱلسَّامُ ٱلْمَوْتُ. وَٱلْحَبَّةُ ٱلسَّوْدَاءُ ٱلشُّونِيزُ.","english":"[…] God’s Prophet (ﷺ) says: “Blackseed is a cure of every disease short of fatality.” Fatality is death, blackseed is swartzcummel."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of سَمَا (samā, “to be high, to be exalted”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of سَمَّ (samma, “to poison”).\n\nBorrowed from Classical Syriac ܣܳܡ (sām, “to constitute, to establish, to set, to place, to install”).\n\nCompare Hebrew שֵׁם (šēm)."},"ipa":["/saː.min/","/saːmm/","/saː.ma/","/saːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20614","headword_ar":"سَامٌّ","root":"sm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~a","text_ar":"سَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as such signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poisoning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infecting with poison"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~apN","text_ar":"سَامَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an act. part. n. [in the fem. form because applied to things of the fem. gender (such as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqorab","text_ar":"عَقْرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.), and to such as are denoted by gen. ns., which are used in a pl. sense], (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are, venomous"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) of animals, (K,) or of creeping things, [and insects,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but of which the venom does not kill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the scorpion, and the hornet: (Msb:) and such things (Sh, Msb) and the like thereof (Sh) are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAm~u","text_ar":"سَوَامُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, Msb,) which is the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~apN","text_ar":"سَامَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~u A^aboraSa","text_ar":"سَامُّ اَبْرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~a A^aboraSa","text_ar":"سَامَّ اَبْرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as one word, (S and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brS","text_ar":"برص"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the latter in the present art. also,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraSa","text_ar":"اَبْرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~u","text_ar":"سَمُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lizard called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wazag","text_ar":"وَزَغ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are large, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wazag","text_ar":"وَزَغ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brS","text_ar":"برص"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Msb:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the large"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wazag","text_ar":"وَزَغ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, K:) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAm~u","text_ar":"السَّامُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA, from a trad.:) [see more in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brS","text_ar":"برص"},{"kind":"text","text":":] applied to the male and the female: (Zj, Msb:) dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~aA A^aboraSa","text_ar":"سَامَّا اَبْرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAm~u A^aboraSa","text_ar":"سَوَامُّ اَبْرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, Mgh, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN saAm~N","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ سَامٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning “ a poisoning day ”] (M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musim~N","text_ar":"مُسِمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, M, K,) the latter rare, (M,) [and anomalous, being from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~a","text_ar":"سُمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masomuwmN","text_ar":"مَسْمُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day attended with the wind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samuwm","text_ar":"سَمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, K.)       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~apN","text_ar":"سَامَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~N","text_ar":"سَامٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as part. n. of the intrans. verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~a","text_ar":"سَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ it was, or became, particular,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1421},{"kind":"text","text":"peculiar, or special. ” And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAm~apu","text_ar":"السَّامَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAS~ap","text_ar":"خَاصَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinguished people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people of distinction;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the particular, peculiar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special, friends, intimates, familiars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, M, IAth, K, TA) of a man; (IAth, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alsum~apu","text_ar":"السُمَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumamN","text_ar":"سُمَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same; (M;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almasam~apu","text_ar":"المَسَمَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEam~apu","text_ar":"المَعَمَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEam~apu","text_ar":"العَمَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~um~apu","text_ar":"السُّمَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the relations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaraAbapu","text_ar":"القَرَابَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choice, relations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu Almasam~api","text_ar":"اَهْلُ المَسَمَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the relations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aqaAribu","text_ar":"الاَقَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAS~ap","text_ar":"خَاصَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above], (El-Umawee, S, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the relations."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa Als~aAm~apu waAlEaAm~apu","text_ar":"كَيْفَ السَّامَّةُ وَالعَامَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How are the people of distinction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the common people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people in general?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafahu AlEam~apu waAls~aAm~apu","text_ar":"عَرَفَهُ العَمَّةُ وَالسَّامَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people in general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the vulgar, and the people of distinction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knew it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","Sh","M","Mgh","Zj","IAar","IAth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20830","headword_ar":"سَامٍ","root":"smw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"High,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lofty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiY~N","text_ar":"سَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAmK","text_ar":"سَوَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; applied to women as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiyapN","text_ar":"سَامِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whence the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAmiY AlT~arofi","text_ar":"سَوَامِى الطَّرْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buDoEN","text_ar":"بُضْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and to irrational animals, as in an instance here following]. One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alquruwmu Als~awaAmiY","text_ar":"القُرُومُ السَّوَامِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stallions"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stallion-camels high in their heads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raising their heads high."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiyaAtN","text_ar":"سَامِيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiyapN","text_ar":"سَامِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] applied to camels,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That raise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raise high, their eyes and their heads."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 791.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadotu mino saAmiY","text_ar":"رَدَدْتُ مِنْ سَامِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tarofihi","text_ar":"طَرْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. an elliptical phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxowatahu","text_ar":"نَخْوَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is expressed in the explanation) or a similar word being understood; i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I repelled the pride,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haughtiness, of him who was lofty in look;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I contracted to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the lofty in look"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his soul, and annulled his pride,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haughtiness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anofi","text_ar":"الاَنْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiY~u","text_ar":"سَمِىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Highnosed"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdainful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scornful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anf","text_ar":"انف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Also act. part. n. of 1 in all its senses. ―         -b3-  And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumaApN","text_ar":"سُمَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) of which it is the sing., (M,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hunters"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going forth to the chase:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hunters in the day-time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"peculiarly: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hunters wearing the socks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stockings, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misomaAp","text_ar":"مِسْمَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21329","headword_ar":"سَامٌ","root":"swm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, M, Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmapN","text_ar":"سَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as its n. un.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) but the former [signifies the same in Pers., and] is said to be not Arabic. (TA.) It is related in a trad., respecting the salutation of the Jews, that they used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAmu Ealayokumo","text_ar":"السَّامُ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death"},{"kind":"text","text":"come"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon you,"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alaAmu Ealayokumo","text_ar":"السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and that he [i. e. Mo- hammad] used to reply,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumo","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; accord. to the generality of the relaters,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEalayokumo","text_ar":"وَعَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but correctly without the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"implies participation: and it is related of 'Áïsheh that she used to say to them,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumu Als~aA^omu waAl*~aA^omu waAll~aEonapu","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمُ السَّاْمُ وَالذَّاْمُ وَاللَّعْنَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as mentioned in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sA^m","text_ar":"سام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the Jews are also related to have said [to the Muslims],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumu Als~aAmu Ald~aAmu","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمُ السَّامُ الدَّامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawotu Ald~aAy^imu","text_ar":"المَوْتُ الدَّايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwm","text_ar":"دوم"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^imN","text_ar":"دَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in that art.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of tree, of which are made the masts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoqaAl","text_ar":"اَدْقَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daqalN","text_ar":"دَقَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of ships:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, M, TA:) accord. to Sh, (TA,) the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayozuraAn","text_ar":"خَيْزُرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA. [And accord. to some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmapN","text_ar":"سَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also has this signification, and the signification expl. in the sentence here next following: but accord. to the text of the K as given in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~aAmapu","text_ar":"وَالسَّامَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been erroneously substistituted in the copies above referred to for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~aAqapu","text_ar":"وَالسَّاقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, by reason of what precedes it, means that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmapN","text_ar":"سَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqapN","text_ar":"سَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and if the former reading were right, the context in the K would imply that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlsAmp","text_ar":"السامة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of a son of Noah, which is incorrect; the name of that son being only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmN","text_ar":"سَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cavity, in the ground, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqorap","text_ar":"نُقْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which water remains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stagnates, and collects."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [For the verb in this explanation, which is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yunoqaEu","text_ar":"يُنْقَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK and in my MS. copy of the K, I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanoqaEu","text_ar":"يَنْقَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A4-  Also a pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] of which the sing. [or n. un.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmapN","text_ar":"سَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Veins of gold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single vein thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vein in a mountain, differing from its"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if running from east to west, not failing of its promise to yield silver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the former, (M,) or latter, (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA;) accord. to As and IAar: (M, TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ingot of gold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veins of gold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver, in the stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rock"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) En-Nábighah El-Jaadee, (M,) or Edh-Dhubyánee, (TA,) uses"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlsAm","text_ar":"السام"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he likens thereto a woman's front teeth in respect of their whiteness: (M, TA:) and Aboo-Sa'eed says that silver is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siymo","text_ar":"سِيمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in Ar."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmN","text_ar":"سَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) but the meaning most commonly known is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) A poet says, (M,) namely, Keys Ibn-El-Khateem, (S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lawa A@n~aka tuloqiY HanoZalFA fawoqa bayoDinaA\n                      \n                     \n                        tadaHoraja Eano *iY saAmihi AlmutaqaAribi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou threwest colocynths upon our helmets, they would roll along from what is gilded thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"they being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near together:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawa A@n~aka","text_ar":"لَوَ ا@نَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo A^an~aka","text_ar":"لَوْ اَنَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmihi","text_ar":"سَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"relates to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byD","text_ar":"بيض"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which are described as] gilded therewith: (S:) the poet is describing the party as being close together in fight, so that colocynths, notwithstanding their smoothness and the evenness of their parts, if they fell upon their heads, would not reach the ground. (Th, S, * M.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","S","M","Mgh","TA","Kr","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}